Philip Morris CR Shareholders Approved Dividend, New Chief

-- B y   L e n k a   P o n i k e l s k a
-- 
2011-04-29T13:30:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-29/philip-morris-cr-shareholders-approved-dividend-new-chief-1-.html
Philip Morris  CR, the Czech unit of
the world’s largest cigarette maker, said shareholders approved
a dividend of 1,260 koruna ($77.5) a share.  The company held an ordinary general meeting of
shareholders today at its headquarters in Kutna Hora, the  Czech
Republic , Philip Morris said in an e-mailed statement.  Shareholders also approved Andras Tovisi as new chief
executive officer, it said. Tovisi, a former head of the
company’s Hungarian unit, replaced Alvise Giustiniani, who
became Phillip Morris’s vice president in south-eastern Asia,
the company said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lenka Ponikelska in Prague 
 lponikelska1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at   jagomez@bloomberg.net  